Nerve damage or diabetic peripheral neuropathy is one of the long-term complication of diabetes. If left untreated, the damage caused by neuropathy can potentially lead to infection and limb amputation. Fortunately, there are several steps you can take to prevent nerve damage. Along with regular foot checks, controlling your blood sugar levels can improve the symptoms of neuropathy and can delay the progression of nerve damage. http://dbts.ca/72my50Azlns

Hi everyone!  I‚Äôm new to the group.  Has anyone experienced nerve pain or burning from taking an SSRI?   I started lexapro in May and five days later started experiencing burning on my arms, hands, chest and face along with tingling.  When I called my doctor she thought it was just my body getting used to lexapro.  Well 8 weeks later the burning still happens every morning and on and off throughout the day.  Last week my doctor switched me to Zoloft (another SSRI) to see if it would work better for me.  She said that if the pain doesn‚Äôt get better in a few weeks that I would come in for testing.
